==English==

====Homophones====
*[[palate]] (''possibly depending on dialect or accent'')
*[[palette]]
*[[pallette]]

===Etymology 1===
From the Middle English ''palet'', from the Old French ''palete''.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ælɪt|-ælɪt]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# a [[portable]] [[platform]], ususally designed to be easily moved by a [[forklift]], on which goods can be stacked or stored.

=====Translations=====
*German: [[Palette]] ''f''
*Swedish: [[pall]] {{c}}
*Finnish: [[kuormalava]]

===Etymology 2===
From the Middle English ''paillet'', from Anglo-Norman ''paillette'' (''bundle of straw''), from ''paille'' (''straw''), from Latin ''palea'' (''chaff'').

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# a straw bed

===Etymology 3===
{{L.}} [[palla]]: to cut; hence a strip of cloth. The diminutive of the [[pale]]. 

#{{heraldry}} A narrow vertical strip.

